Run dispatches on args[0] to init, todo, reset, link, unlink, list, show, diff, help, skill, config, or version. No args, --help, -h, and help all print the help text with exit code 0. Unknown commands return an error message with help text and exit code 1. Missing args for reset/link/unlink/show/diff return a usage message with an example and exit code 1. Reset accepts 1 arg (a closure hash) plus optional --dry-run. Diff accepts 1 arg (a closure hash) or `--all`. Link and unlink accept marker+spec args plus optional --dry-run. Before any subcommand dispatches, three uniform checks run: (0) global_flag_stripping removes --json/--no-color/--color= from args (see <ref spec="output.global_flags">global flags</ref>), (1) the help_flag check, and (2) the unknown_flag_rejection check. All run for every subcommand including those that take no arguments (init, todo, skill). The version command flows through dispatch like every other command (see <ref spec="output.version_in_dispatch">version in dispatch</ref>).